urls.title: The association between first abortion and first-time non-fatal suicide attempt: a longitudinal cohort study of Danish population registries
urls.description: We found that women who had abortions had a higher risk of non-fatal suicide attempts compared with women who did not have an abortion. However, because the increased risk was the same both the year before and after the abortion, it is not attributable to the abortion. Thus, policies based on the notion that abortion increases women's risk of suicide attempts are misinformed.
